text.tspan: Antibiotic use in livestock vs. GDP per capita, 2010
Antibiotic use in livestock, measured as the milligrams of total active ingredient used per kilogram of meat production
versus gross domestic product (GDP) per capita.
Source: European Medicines Agency, European Surveillance of Veterinary Antimicrobial Consumption (2017), and Van Boeckel et al. (2015);
Data compiled from multiple sources by World Bank
Note: GDP per capita is adjusted for inflation and for differences in the cost of living between countries.
